[1] DESCRIPTION --------------------------------------------------------------

Command-line utility for automated creation and maintenance of source code
modules.

[2] VERSION ------------------------------------------------------------------

0.0.2.1

[3] AUTHORS ------------------------------------------------------------------

Kostya Zolotarov <kostya.zolotarov@gmail.com>

[4] BACKGROUND ---------------------------------------------------------------

I needed a tool to automate creation and maintenance of source code modules.
Invoked from command line, such tool had to produce a source code module.
Produced source code module had to contain a fixed set of templated descriptor
files. These templated and automatically generated descriptor files would
define format and structure of the source code module.

From a high level view, my source module had to have the following file
structure:

.
|
+--- ./DESCRIPTION
|
+--- ./VERSION
|
+--- ./AUTHORS
|
+--- ./CHANGELOG
|
+--- ./TASKS
|
+--- ./DEFECTS
|
+--- ./BUILD
|
+--- ./INSTALL
|
+--- ./LICENSES
|
+--- ./.settings
|
+--- etc.

[5] SOURCES ------------------------------------------------------------------

Source code can be obtained on GitHub (https://github.com/kz9676/srcmod).

Presently, I have one active branch:

    * origin/development  - is the main branch where the source code of HEAD
                            always reflects a state with the latest delivered
                            development changes for the next release

I often use supporting branches to aid parallel development, tracking of
features, preparation for production release and quick fixes for live
production defects. Supporting branches may include the following:

    * Feature branches
    * Release branches
    * Hotfix branches

